<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="hurry-n">hurry <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'hʌri/    美 /'hɜːri/  </p>
<p>[U]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>匆忙；仓促：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Take your time; <strong>there is no hurry</strong>.
慢慢来，不用急。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="in-a-ones-hurry">in a / one's hurry</h3>
<p>1.<strong>匆忙；急于：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He was in a hurry to leave.
他急着要离开。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In his hurry to catch the train, he left his book in the taxi.
他匆匆忙忙地去赶火车，把书落在了出租车里。</p></div>

<h3 id="in-no-hurry">in no hurry</h3>
<p>1.<strong>不着急：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I don't mind waiting — I'm in no hurry / I'm not in a hurry.
我可以等，我不着急。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">派生词汇</h2>
<p>hurried /'hʌrid/ adj   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>eat a hurried meal
匆匆吃一顿饭</p></div>

<p>hurriedly /'hʌridli/ adv   </p>
<h2 id="_4">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>— OK, I'll fix your computer right now.<br />
— Oh, take your time. I'm <strong><em>_</em></strong>____ no hurry.   （2014 天津改）  </li>
<li>— Thank you for your MP4 player. I'll ask Mary to take it to you soon.
— <strong><em>_</em></strong>_（不着急）. I've bought a new one.  （2009 江西）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. in  2. No hurry / rush  </p></div>